Financial services provider, Jaiz Bank, has assured its customers of better services as it has upgraded its system. While the upgrade lasted, customers of the bank experienced services disruption, but that has been resolved, said the bank. Some customers had recently experienced services failure and had complained about it, saying it caused them great discomfort. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The bank had in June, 2019, notified its customers of the impending upgrade and apologised. The bank had said in a notice, “Dear esteemed customer, due to system upgrade, access to our e-channels will not be available on 22/06/19 (2am – 6pm). We apologise for the inconvenience.” But some customers still had issues after the period the bank said the system would be down. The bank’s spokesman, Mr. Idris Ahmed, told our correspondent on phone that the bank had returned to seamless operations. Mr. Ahmed confirmed that while the system upgrade lasted, customers could not access some of the bank’s services. He said if any customer still had issues, it might be peculiar to that particular customer, and that therefore, they should approach the nearest branch for the issue to be resolved. System upgrade: Ecobank reassures customers of improved services As deadline for bank verification number draws near Massive sack as strong banks acquire weak ones Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin